  "texts": [
    "Initially, when the point space is sparsely populated, the introduction of each new point markedly influences the diversity, resulting in relatively high rewards at the outset.",
    "This effect diminishes over time as more points fill the space, making each new point's contribution to diversity less impactful compared to the early stages.",
    "However, it is noteworthy that the reward does not significantly decrease; instead, it stabilizes and, towards the latter stages, even increases.",
    "This trend suggests that as the algorithm progresses, the execution time increases meaning the algorithm is doing well in finding inputs causing more execution times.",
    "The pronounced dips observed in the reward function are indicative of collision events."
  ],
